Dear All:



After around a year of dwelling on the concept, I now have quikscript.org
working.  The primary goal is to have a threaded forum where everyone can
use embedded fonts and read and write about QS by actually using it.  I have
two fonts currently, the latest incarnation of King Plus Mono and Suave. 



Through making surgical changes in forum style sheets and javascript (which
I notice Mr. Sharfi has also done on his blog), I believe it is stable but
requires an &quot;up-to-date&quot; browser.  I tested on my phone and it also renders
well and is readable. 



Testing is never complete so I&#39;m open to suggestions for improvements, bug
fixes, additions, etc.  Sadly, my skills in reading and writing software
still surpasses my ability to read and write in quikscript, but I hope the
forum will remedy this deficiency.



I hope others can give it a try and chat in quikscript.



Jayson


